entry.title: Replace most source-registration waits in WPT with redirect chains
entry.content:
In addition to providing test coverage of the ability to register

sources and/or triggers in each response of a chain, this allows us to

remove the explicit waits for source registration to occur, because

registrations in a chain are guaranteed to be processed in order.



We cannot do this in all cases, as navigation-source API surfaces are

incapable of registering triggers.



We deliberately separate the creation of the redirect-chain URL from

initiating the request to make it easier to reuse logic for

multiple background attributionsrc requests in a followup CL.

entry.title: FLEDGE: Add ability to translate currencies for reporting in multi-currency auctions
entry.content:
This is conditional on auction configuration setting sellerCurrency; if it's not set the behavior is as previous, except some reporting functions get an extra currency signal passed in that will be '???'.



If sellerCurrency is set, the scoring function can provide conversion of bids not already in that currency into it (as incomingBidInSellerCurrency), which will be shared with reporting functions along with the corresponding currency tag. If no conversion is provided they see a 0 for the value.



The exception is the winningBid for reportWin, which will always be unaltered, and can receive an accurate bidCurrency if perBuyerCurrencies for it is specified, otherwise also getting '???'.



As of this CL, private aggregation is not fully updated for sellerCurrency-enabled mode.



As OnScoreAdComplete is being changed anyway, make it use an optional primitive rather than separate bool now that's possible.



Context for this work is https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/issues/166

entry.title: Implement CompositeBackgroundAttachmentFixed
entry.content:
This implements composited background-attachment:fixed when possible.

With this feature enabled, if all background-attachment:fixed

backgrounds in a frame are composited, the scrollers in the frame

won't need repaint on scroll or main-thread scrolling.



When possible, background-attachment:fixed background is painted

- in the view's transform space;

- the display item fills the whole view;

- clipped by BackgroundClip (a new paint property node).

entry.title: [sync] Encapsulate sync-requested in SyncServiceImpl
entry.content:
No behavioral changes, pure refactoring.



Leftover references to the concept of sync-requested are removed

from SyncUserSettingsImpl, and all writes are now "directly" issued from

SyncServiceImpl. In truth, there is still the SyncPrefs layer between

SyncServiceImpl and PrefService, but avoiding this requires too much

temporary boilerplate (pref registration code) for a concept that should

go away soon.



With this patch, SyncServiceImpl does assume it is the only writer to

the pref, and stops observing changes to it. This simplifies the logic

that follows a pref change, because it becomes more obvious from the

calling site what can actually happen. Namely, one redundant call

to ResetEngine() with STOP_SYNC_AND_KEEP_DATA is removed.

entry.title: Fix BlockFrameRenavigations
entry.content:
This kill switch for this was turned off in M112 because server

redirects are considered as having the same InitiatorFrameToken as the

navigation that preceeded them, so we were detecting them as cross-frame

re-navigations even through it's really the frame navigating itself.



This change excludes redirects from being considered as cross-frame

re-navigations and tracks whether something along the redirect chain was

previously considered a re-navigation to avoid client redirects allowing

external navigation after a cross-frame re-navigation.

.GlobalPreferences_m.plist makes up the second part of a so-called

even if they're somehow deleted from .GlobalPreferences.plist.

CFPreferences accesses both files in the mirrored source simultaneously,

so we should allow access to it as we do .GlobalPreferences.plist.

This finch-controllable threshold must be exceeded as well as the %

but the 128Gb machine would start discarding when it has 1Gb available.

entry.title: [BSC]: Fix failing BSC `GoogleURLLoader` unittests
entry.content:
`net::cookie_util::IsDomainMatch` relies that the domain has a '.'

prefix. Therefore, it return false for `accounts.google.com` and

`google.com`. This CL uses `GURL::DomainIs` to ensure bound session

requests are correctly blocked when the cookie is expired.



`BoundSessionParams::domain` reflects a domain that is configured by

Gaia as part of the registration flow for a bound session. It instructs

the browser on which request requires the short lived cookie regardless

of the actual domain of the cookie. At this point

`BoundSessionParams::domain` is set based on

`GaiaUrls::GetInstance()->secure_google_url()` as the registration flow

is not implemented yet and does not contain a '.' prefix.

entry.title: Fix Autofill address callback in Settings.
entry.content:
The bug is reproducible after opening an Incognito window.

PDM::Init() call in the Incognito mode is called with the same instances

of `AutofillWebDataService` (`profile_database`, `account_database`) as

the origin profile (this is how `chrome::GetBrowserContextRedirectedInIncognito(context)`

works, see `WebDataServiceFactory::GetAutofillWebDataForProfile` and

`WebDataServiceFactory::GetBrowserContextToUse`) overriding the

`on_autofill_profile_changed_cb_` callback in

`AutofillWebDataBackendImpl`.



Hence the symptoms: added addresses are not lost, Sync knows about

updates, but updates do not appear on the page until `PDM::Refresh()`

is called somewhere (e.g. by adding a Credit card).

entry.title: dlp: Make warning modal to the Files app
entry.content:
Modifies DLP Files warning dialog to be modal to the Files app, if one

is opened. If no windows can be found, the dialog is created as a

system modal. This will be changed to open a new Files app instance in

later CLs.



Currently, the Files app window is detected in the DlpFilesController,

when processing requests for file open/share, drag n drop, transfer.

When we support the new notifications which allow the user to "Review",

we can pass the exact Files app window in which the notification was

handled and use this as the modal parent.



When no opened Files app windows can be found (e.g. when "Review"-ing

from a system notification), we will still retrieve the last active

Files app window, or create a new one.
